22/07/2003
BRUSSELS, Belgium -- Hungary expressed its willingness Monday (21 July) to take part in EU accession talks with Bulgaria and Romania.
Hungarian government representative Endre Juhasz told a meeting of EU foreign ministers in Brussels that the ten countries which are joining the Union should be included in negotiations with the new candidates.The ten countries set to join next May are Hungary, the Czech Republic, Poland, Slovakia, Slovenia, Estonia, Latvia, Lithuania, Cyprus and Malta.
Juhasz said discussion with the two candidates scheduled to enter the Union in 2007 was necessary, as Hungary must ratify their accession protocols in the future.
(Kossuth Radio, BTA - 21/07/03)
